HEADWORD: Womankind
<hw>Wom"an*kind`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The females of
the human race; women, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A sanctuary into which <qex>womankind</qex>, with her tools of
magic, the broom and mop, has very infrequent access.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Womanless</ent>⟦br⟧
